to exist to do what they do.

00:12:13.820 --> 00:12:16.200 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And who
do they report to?

00:12:16.200 --> 00:12:19.850 align:middle line:84%
>>PHILLIPS: Well, every
government agency,

00:12:19.850 --> 00:12:21.770 align:middle line:84%
whether it's the
CIA, or the FBI,

00:12:21.770 --> 00:12:24.020 align:middle line:84%
or NSA, or military
intelligence,

00:12:24.020 --> 00:12:25.380 align:middle line:90%
has chains of command.

00:12:25.380 --> 00:12:27.960 align:middle line:84%
But inside those
organizations, there

00:12:27.960 --> 00:12:31.530 align:middle line:84%
are units of activity
that are semi-independent.

00:12:31.530 --> 00:12:33.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They're
rogue, aren't they?

00:12:33.030 --> 00:12:35.630 align:middle line:84%
>>PHILLIPS: Well, "rogue"
is an interesting word.

00:12:35.630 --> 00:12:37.740 align:middle line:84%
If they get caught, then
they say they're rogue.

00:12:37.740 --> 00:12:43.320 align:middle line:84%
But they are institutionalized
inside of these organizations.

00:12:43.320 --> 00:12:45.500 align:middle line:84%
And there's money
