>>PHILLIPS: 800 tons of--

00:13:19.030 --> 00:13:22.640 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And it's all
illegal drug money.

00:13:22.640 --> 00:13:24.570 align:middle line:90%
What do they do with the money?

00:13:24.570 --> 00:13:27.050 align:middle line:84%
>>PHILLIPS: It goes
in the central banks.

00:13:27.050 --> 00:13:30.910 align:middle line:84%
In 2008, with the crisis we
had, the collapse of the housing

00:13:30.910 --> 00:13:33.320 align:middle line:84%
market, it was the
drug money that kind of

00:13:33.320 --> 00:13:35.450 align:middle line:90%
kept the banks afloat.

00:13:35.450 --> 00:13:36.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Amazing.

00:13:36.600 --> 00:13:38.290 align:middle line:90%
The public doesn't get it.

00:13:38.290 --> 00:13:40.655 align:middle line:84%
>>PHILLIPS: Half
a billion-- no, I

00:13:40.655 --> 00:13:43.800 align:middle line:84%
mean half a trillion-- dollars
in drug money annually.

00:13:43.800 --> 00:13:49.660 align:middle line:84%
And so it's like-- the DEA is
trying to control drugs, right?

00:13:49.660 --> 00:13:50.460 align:middle line:90%
That's their job.

00:13:50.460 --> 00:13:51.750 align:middle line:90%
That's their task force.

00:13:51.750 --> 00:13:53.750 align:middle line:84%
But in Honduras, or
