with propaganda films.

00:30:55.075 --> 00:30:56.700 align:middle line:84%
>>PHILLIPS: They had
plenty of it then,

00:30:56.700 --> 00:30:59.340 align:middle line:90%
but they're more subtle now.

00:30:59.340 --> 00:31:02.670 align:middle line:84%
And so you have these massive
public relations and propaganda

00:31:02.670 --> 00:31:05.014 align:middle line:84%
film that are interwoven
with government.

00:31:05.014 --> 00:31:07.430 align:middle line:84%
And they're the ones doing all
the advertising for product

00:31:07.430 --> 00:31:09.320 align:middle line:90%
management and stuff like that.

00:31:09.320 --> 00:31:10.930 align:middle line:84%
Our new study
coming out this year

00:31:10.930 --> 00:31:12.870 align:middle line:84%
is going to-- we looked
at all their clients.

00:31:12.870 --> 00:31:14.190 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it's just amazing.

00:31:14.190 --> 00:31:16.770 align:middle line:84%
Any supermarket you walk
into, everything there

00:31:16.770 --> 00:31:19.360 align:middle line:84%
is managed by one of those three
firms in terms of their PR.

00:31:19.360 --> 00:31:21.450 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: And how to do
it, placement, everything.

00:31:21.450 --> 00:31:22.190 align:middle line:10%
>>PHILLIPS: Everything.

00:31:22.190 --> 00:31:23.110 align:middle line:10%
It's just huge.

00:31:23.110 --> 00:31:26.420 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: They know human
psychology, don't they?

00:31:26.420 --> 00:31:27.890 align:middle line:90%
>>PHILLIPS: Yeah, very much so.

00:31:27.890 --> 00:31:32.350 align:middle line:84%
And so they're in service to the
transnational capitalist class,

00:31:32.350 --> 00:31:35.000 align:middle line:90%
as are mercenary companies.

00:31:35.000 --> 00:31:44.820 align:middle line:84%
The second largest employer in
the world is WG4-- sorry, G4S.

00:31:44.820 --> 00:31:48.450 align:middle line:90%
They employ 600,000 people.

00:31:48.450 --> 00:31:49.790 align:middle line:90%
They're a securities firm.

