they hire them.

00:32:20.840 --> 00:32:23.030 align:middle line:84%
>>PHILLIPS: They hire them
to protect themselves.

00:32:23.030 --> 00:32:27.200 align:middle line:84%
So it's like, if you're
incredibly wealthy,

00:32:27.200 --> 00:32:28.810 align:middle line:84%
you can hire people
to protect you.

00:32:28.810 --> 00:32:31.200 align:middle line:84%
You can create your
own green zone,

00:32:31.200 --> 00:32:37.880 align:middle line:84%
and literally separate yourself
from the rest of the world.

00:32:37.880 --> 00:32:43.650 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Dwight Eisenhower, when
he left office back in 1961,

00:32:43.650 --> 00:32:46.000 align:middle line:84%
of course, when he
turned the gauntlet over

00:32:46.000 --> 00:32:50.330 align:middle line:84%
to John F. Kennedy, warned us
about the military-industrial

00:32:50.330 --> 00:32:51.130 align:middle line:90%
complex.

00:32:51.130 --> 00:32:52.805 align:middle line:90%


00:32:52.805 --> 00:32:54.180 align:middle line:84%
>>DWIGHT EISENHOWER:
We have been

00:32:54.180 --> 00:32:56.560 align:middle line:84%
compelled to create
a permanent armaments

00:32:56.560 --> 00:32:59.620 align:middle line:90%
industry of vast proportions.

00:32:59.620 --> 00:33:03.900 align:middle line:84%
Added to this, 3 and 1/2
million men and women

00:33:03.900 --> 00:33:07.730 align:middle line:84%
are directly engaged in
the defense establishment.

00:33:07.730 --> 00:33:10.820 align:middle line:84%
We annually spend,
on military security

00:33:10.820 --> 00:33:15.770 align:middle line:84%
alone, more than the net
income of all United States

00:33:15.770 --> 00:33:17.990 align:middle line:90%
corporations.

00:33:17.990 --> 00:33:21.110 align:middle line:84%
Now, this conjunction of an
immense military establishment

00:33:21.110 --> 00:33:26.910 align:middle line:84%
and a large arms industry is
new in the American experience.

00:33:26.910 --> 00:33:32.170 align:middle line:84%
The total influence, economic,
political, even spiritual,

00:33:32.170 --> 00:33:35.980 align:middle line:84%
is felt in every city, every
state house, every office

00:33:35.980 --> 00:33:38.210 align:middle line:90%
of the federal government.

00:33:38.210 --> 00:33:41.890 align:middle line:84%
We recognize the imperative
need for this development,

00:33:41.890 --> 00:33:44.630 align:middle line:84%
yet we must not
fail to comprehend

00:33:44.630 --> 00:33:47.130 align:middle line:90%
its grave implications.

00:33:47.130 --> 00:33:51.680 align:middle line:84%
Our toil, resources, and
livelihood are all involved.

00:33:51.680 --> 00:33:55.430 align:middle line:84%
So in the very structure
of our society.

00:33:55.430 --> 00:33:57.360 align:middle line:84%
In the councils
of government, we

00:33:57.360 --> 00:34:00.320 align:middle line:84%
must guard against
the acquisition

00:34:00.320 --> 00:34:03.990 align:middle line:84%
of unwarranted influence,
whether sought or unsought,

00:34:03.990 --> 00:34:07.640 align:middle line:84%
by the military-industrial
complex.

00:34:07.640 --> 00:34:10.969 align:middle line:84%
The potential for the disastrous
rise of misplaced power

00:34:10.969 --> 00:34:14.230 align:middle line:90%
exists and will persist.

00:34:14.230 --> 00:34:16.699 align:middle line:84%
We must never let the
weight of this combination

00:34:16.699 --> 00:34:21.069 align:middle line:84%
endanger our liberties
or democratic processes.

00:34:21.069 --> 00:34:22.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Isn't that
incredible coming

00:34:22.610 --> 00:34:27.065 align:middle line:84%
from a person who was a
general during World War II?

00:34:27.065 --> 00:34:29.190 align:middle line:84%
>>PHILLIPS: It was an
amazing statement, certainly,

00:34:29.190 --> 00:34:33.130 align:middle line:84%
at the time, and of course,
has manifested itself

00:34:33.130 --> 00:34:37.570 align:middle line:84%
as being true or
even beyond that now.

00:34:37.570 --> 00:34:41.339 align:middle line:84%
And I don't think we
took it seriously enough.

00:34:41.339 --> 00:34:42.139 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: No.

00:34:42.139 --> 00:34:46.000 align:middle line:84%
>>PHILLIPS: The next president
did, and paid with it

00:34:46.000 --> 00:34:47.115 align:middle line:90%
for his life.

00:34:47.115 --> 00:34:50.139 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Yeah, no
question about that.

00:34:50.139 --> 00:34:53.960 align:middle line:84%
At this point today, if you
listen to Eisenhower's words

00:34:53.960 --> 00:34:58.360 align:middle line:84%
and apply it to what's
going on now, he was right.

00:34:58.360 --> 00:35:00.256 align:middle line:90%
He was right on, wasn't he?

00:35:00.256 --> 00:35:02.880 align:middle line:84%
>>PHILLIPS: Well, he was right--
certainly, yeah, under Truman,

00:35:02.880 --> 00:35:04.990 align:middle line:84%
the National Security
Act was passed

00:35:04.990 --> 00:35:07.860 align:middle line:84%
that created the CIA,
which is kind of an OSS.

00:35:07.860 --> 00:35:10.530 align:middle line:84%
