were involved.

00:35:10.530 --> 00:35:15.690 align:middle line:84%
They were pretty much running
State and the CIA together.

00:35:15.690 --> 00:35:17.890 align:middle line:84%
So they were there
the deep state.

00:35:17.890 --> 00:35:20.050 align:middle line:90%
They were the ones pushing it.

00:35:20.050 --> 00:35:23.220 align:middle line:84%
So it's no accident that
Dulles ran the commission

00:35:23.220 --> 00:35:29.580 align:middle line:84%
after Kennedy was assassination,
the investigation, so to speak.

00:35:29.580 --> 00:35:32.020 align:middle line:84%
So they were very powerful
people at that time.

00:35:32.020 --> 00:35:34.150 align:middle line:84%
And they worked directly
for major corporations

00:35:34.150 --> 00:35:36.460 align:middle line:84%
of the world, and
brought about coups

00:35:36.460 --> 00:35:41.280 align:middle line:84%
in Guatemala and other
places, certainly, in Iran.

00:35:41.280 --> 00:35:45.345 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did Kennedy have
to go according to them?

00:35:45.345 --> 00:35:46.970 align:middle line:84%
>>PHILLIPS: Definitely,
I think he did.

00:35:46.970 --> 00:35:49.290 align:middle line:84%
Because he was
challenging the CIA.

00:35:49.290 --> 00:35:52.060 align:middle line:84%
He wasn't going to go
along with a global war

00:35:52.060 --> 00:35:54.880 align:middle line:90%
process of expanding military.

00:35:54.880 --> 00:35:57.470 align:middle line:84%
And he was seriously
thinking about getting out

00:35:57.470 --> 00:36:01.050 align:middle line:84%
of and diminishing our
involvement in Vietnam.

00:36:01.050 --> 00:36:05.250 align:middle line:90%
So that was a strong counter.

00:36:05.250 --> 00:36:08.385 align:middle line:84%
But he particularly wanted
to dismantle the CIA.

00:36:08.385 --> 00:36:11.750 align:middle line:84%
He thought that they were a
threat to American freedoms.

00:36:11.750 --> 00:36:12.940 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: He was right.

00:36:12.940 --> 00:36:14.560 align:middle line:10%
>>PHILLIPS: He was very right.

00:36:14.560 --> 00:36:16.085 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: And he paid for it.

00:36:16.085 --> 00:36:17.280 align:middle line:10%
>>PHILLIPS: He paid for it.

00:36:17.280 --> 00:36:17.780 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: And his
brother paid for it.

00:36:17.780 --> 00:36:19.988 align:middle line:10%
>>PHILLIPS: His brother paid
for it, yes, absolutely.

00:36:19.988 --> 00:36:23.610 align:middle line:10%
David Talbot's work on
that, "The Brothers,"

00:36:23.610 --> 00:36:25.440 align:middle line:10%
I have my students read
that in my classes,

00:36:25.440 --> 00:36:26.942 align:middle line:10%
and it's an amazing work.

00:36:26.942 --> 00:36:29.400 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Yeah, David's been a
guest on the "Coast to Coast"

00:36:29.400 --> 00:36:30.200 align:middle line:90%
radio show.

00:36:30.200 --> 00:36:31.640 align:middle line:90%
He's a great person.

00:36:31.640 --> 00:36:33.097 align:middle line:90%
>>PHILLIPS: He's a good scholar.

00:36:33.097 --> 00:36:34.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So where do
we go from here, Peter?

00:36:34.930 --> 00:36:35.950 align:middle line:90%
What happens next?

00:36:35.950 --> 00:36:37.325 align:middle line:84%
>>PHILLIPS: Well,
it's inevitable

00:36:37.325 --> 00:36:40.180 align:middle line:84%
that democracy movements
are going to continue

00:36:40.180 --> 00:36:42.680 align:middle line:90%
to arise all over the world.

00:36:42.680 --> 00:36:44.280 align:middle line:84%
It's inevitable
that capital will

00:36:44.280 --> 00:36:46.639 align:middle line:84%
become so concentrated
that they're not

00:36:46.639 --> 00:36:47.680 align:middle line:90%
going to have some place.

00:36:47.680 --> 00:36:50.640 align:middle line:84%
So we're going to see
continuing economic crises.

00:36:50.640 --> 00:36:52.640 align:middle line:90%
So they're speculating.

00:36:52.640 --> 00:36:55.380 align:middle line:84%
There's bubbles
all over the place

00:36:55.380 --> 00:37:00.420 align:middle line:84%
in terms of various commodities,
or land, or water, or whatever.

00:37:00.420 --> 00:37:02.480 align:middle line:90%
Those are not sustainable.

00:37:02.480 --> 00:37:05.040 align:middle line:84%
So there's going to be
continuing economic unrest

00:37:05.040 --> 00:37:06.484 align:middle line:90%
in a variety of ways.

00:37:06.484 --> 00:37:08.900 align:middle line:84%
It's going to be harder and
harder for, like, young people

00:37:08.900 --> 00:37:13.810 align:middle line:84%
today to get jobs that will get
them out of their college debt,

00:37:13.810 --> 00:37:16.890 align:middle line:84%
and have them be able to buy
a home, and have a family.

00:37:16.890 --> 00:37:18.240 align:middle line:90%
It's just not going to happen.

